latestPosts.caption:
Soft days, small adventures, and pieces we actually live in.

Our mornings lately have been slow and sweet.  They're all about dressed, packing snacks, and finding the sun.
We’ve been loving this little @bergportugal camping trolley I found at @continente as its perfect for beach days, park hangs, and market mornings.

I’m in my usual mix of @hm and @mango and Ezra’s in his comfy @tiptoeyjoey shoes.

#familydays #lisbonwithkids #sundaymood #bergportugal #hmxme #mangogirls #tiptoeyjoey

Two years ago, @hushofficial was the first brand I said yes to after becoming a mother. I went scared, unsure, and sleep-deprived but Kyle encouraged me to go. Last Saturday he went on my behalf as I rest and recover in Lisbon from my corneal transplant rejection and mental health struggles.

 I’ll always hold this brand close for the quiet ways it’s been there.

Is this the cutest thing ever or what?

latestPosts.caption:
slow mornings + soft brushstrokes 

We've been leaning into a rhythm that feels more intuitive lately by being barefoot on the terrace, painting with our fingers and feeling no pressure to colour inside the lines.

This little painting set from @lidlportugal was such a beautiful find - proof that sustainable and Montessori inspired moments don't 
need to be expensive, just intentional.

This is our reminder to nurture curiosity, embrace the mess
and let our little one's lead the way.

#montessori  #montessoriathome #montessoriano #montessoriactivities  #childled #sustainableparenting #ezrasdays

latestPosts.caption:
Ezra said lellow yesterday and it took me back to this day. 💛 

We hadn’t all been together like this in over five weeks until this day.
Not just in the same place — but really together.

This day in Sintra was the first time it felt like we could breathe again.
The three of us. Holding hands, walking slowly, letting the sun find us.

There’s something sacred about family reunions. Not the big dramatic kind, but the quiet ones. A shared sandwich. A laugh from the stroller. A familiar hand reaching for yours.

So many families are learning how to move through distance, work, travel, life.
If you’re in it...I see you. It’s not easy. But the coming back?
It’s everything.

Can't wait to see my darling husband again. Whenever logistics, finances and visas and God make a way so we can feel each other again. 

Love you Ky,

Your Issy
